        <IsA>library</IsA>
        <Summary>A Python binding to exiv2</Summary>
        <Description>pyexiv2 is a Python binding to exiv2, the C++ library for manipulation of EXIF, IPTC and XMP image metadata. It is a python module that allows your python scripts to read and write metadata (EXIF, IPTC, XMP, thumbnails) embedded in image files (JPEG, TIFF, ...). It is designed as a high-level interface to the functionalities offered by libexiv2. Using python's built-in data types and standard modules, it provides easy manipulation of image metadata.</Description>
